The following repository has two subfolders:

V1 - Basic loader to execute a DLL payload
V2 - Fully reflective loader designed for evasion purposes (in-memory execution)

How to use it manually:

Upload or place the ASPX file in any IIS web root folder.

Access the page through your browser using: page.aspx?k=SECRET

Upload or provide your payload in Base64 format and make sure to specify the exported function in the function export field.

Execute and wait.

Can I use it with C2?

I released another tool called "PhantomLink" to perform that task. You can use it for lateral movement or host infection.
